### JWT Authentication Tests

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7146
@token = 

### 1. Login - Generate JWT Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "demo123"
}

### 2. Get Current User Info (Protected - Requires Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Validate Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{token}}"
}

### 4. Test Unauthorized Access (No Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me

### 5. Test with Invalid Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### 6. Test Expired Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ.SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c

